domain.location

Class DiagonalLocationPair

  • java.lang.Object
    • domain.location.LocationPair
      • domain.location.DiagonalLocationPair

  • public class DiagonalLocationPair
extends LocationPair
    A special variant of LocationPair where both Locations are forced to lie on the same diagonal.

    • Method Detail

      • getDiagonalDistance

        public int getDiagonalDistance()
        Returns the diagonal distance between the two Locations, which happens to coincide with both the row and the column distance.

      • getCenterBetween

        public Location getCenterBetween()
        Returns the Location of the ISquare in the middle of this DiagonalLocationPair. This method only supports DiagonalLocationPairs with a diagonal distance of two.

      • getLocationsBetweenStrict

      • getStepsBetweenStrict

        public java.util.List<DiagonalLocationPair> getStepsBetweenStrict()
        Returns a list of consecutive DiagonalLocationPairs (i.e. steps) of diagonal distance two that, when added together, span all Locations strictly between this DiagonalLocationPair.

      • getStepsBetween

        public java.util.List<DiagonalLocationPair> getStepsBetween()
        Returns a list of consecutive DiagonalLocationPairs (i.e. steps) of diagonal distance two that, when added together, span all Locations between this DiagonalLocationPair.
